Claims CLAIMS What is claimed is: 1. A method for coordinating at least two applications, comprising: detecting a touch input at a device location associated with a first application; monitoring for a related touch input ending at a device location associated with the second application, wherein one of the first and second applications is a user authentication application; detecting the related touch input at the device location associated with the second application, establishing at least one parameter with the user authentication application; and running one of the first and second applications that is not the user authentication application with the at least one parameter. 2. The method of claim 1, wherein the user authentication application comprises a fingerprint detector. 3. The method of claim 2, wherein one of the device locations associated with the first and second applications is configured as a fingerprint sensor. 4. The method of claim 3, wherein each of the device locations associated with the first and second applications are on a single device surface. 5. The method of claim 4, wherein each of the device locations associated with the first and second applications are on a single display screen. 6. The method of claim 5, wherein the device location configured to sense fingerprints is variable. 7. The method of claim 4, wherein the related touch input ending at the device location associated with the second application comprises a swipe that continues from the detected touch input at the device location associated with the first application. 8. The method of claim 3, wherein the first application is the user authentication application. 9 The method of claim 8, wherein the at least one parameter established by the user authentication application is a user verification if the fingerprint sensor detects a matching fingerprint and if the related touch input is continuously completed. 10. The method of claim 3, wherein the second application is the user authentication application. 1 1. The method of claim 10, wherein the at least one parameter is based at least in part on a request from the first application. 12. The method of claim 10, further comprising operating the user authentication application based at least in part on the detection of touch input at the device location associated with the first application. 13. The method of claim 12, wherein operating the user authentication application is also based on detection of a user input pattern that matches a beginning of the related touch input. 14. The method of claim 12, wherein operating the user authentication application comprises activating at least one hardware component. 15. The method of claim 14, wherein activating at least one hardware component comprises calibrating the fingerprint sensor. 16. The method of claim 14, wherein activating at least one hardware component comprises adjusting operation of the fingerprint sensor. 17. The method of claim 16, wherein adjusting operation of the fingerprint sensor is based on the related touch input. 18. The method of claim 3, wherein each of the device locations associated 

 with the first and second applications are on opposing device surfaces. 19. The method of claim 18, wherein the related touch input comprises a touch input that occurs at a same time as the detected touch input. 20. The method of claim 1, wherein the user authentication application is configured to recognize a user input to verify identification. 21. The method of claim 1, further comprising a visual indication of the coordination between the first and second applications. 22. The method of claim 21, wherein the visual indication signals the device locations associated with the first and second applications. 23. The method of claim 2, wherein at least one of the device locations associated with the first and second applications is determined based on the position of the fingerprint sensor. 24. The method of claim 1, further comprising providing a visual indication when the touch input is detected at the device location associated with the first application. 25. The method of claim 24, wherein providing a visual indication when the touch input is detected at the device location associated with the first application comprises providing a visual indication at the device location associated with the second application. 26. The method of claim 24, wherein providing a visual indication when the touch input is detected at the device location associated with the first application comprises providing a visual indication on a remote display. 27. A user interface for a device having a touch-based input, wherein the interface is configured to: detect a touch input at a device location associated with a first application; 

 monitor for a related touch input ending at a device location associated with the second application, wherein one of the first and second applications is a user authentication application; detect the related touch input at the device location associated with the second application; establish at least one parameter with the user authentication application; and run one of the first and second applications that is not the user authentication application with the at least one parameter. 28. A device for coordinating at least two applications, comprising: a touch screen; a fingerprint sensor; and a processor operable to: detect a touch input at a device location associated with a first application; monitor for a related touch input ending at a device location associated with the second application, wherein one of the first and second applications is a user authentication application, wherein at least one of the device location associated with the first application and the device location associated with the second application are on the touch screen and wherein at least one of the device location associated with the first application and the device location associated with the second application comprise the fingerprint sensor; detect the related touch input at the device location associated with the second application; establish at least one parameter with the user authentication application; and run one of the first and second applications that is not the user authentication application with the at least one parameter. 29. The device of claim 28, wherein the fingerprint sensor is mounted adjacent to the touch screen of the device. 30. The device of claim 28, wherein the fingerprint sensor is mounted behind the touch screen of the device. 3 1. The device of claim 28, wherein the fingerprint sensor is integrated with the touch screen of the device. 32. The device of claim 28, wherein the authentication application selects the fingerprint sensor based on one of the first and second application. 33. The device of claim 28, wherein operation of the fingerprint sensor is based at least in part on one of the first application and detection of the touch input at the device location associated with the first application.
